The '''Puerto Rico Science, Technology and Research Trust''' is a private non-profit organization created in 2004 to encourage and promote innovation, transfer and commercialization of technology and creation of jobs in the technology sector, based in [[San Juan, Puerto Rico|San Juan]], [[Puerto Rico]].<ref>{{cite web| url=http://eventful.com/sanjuan/venues/puerto-rico-science-technology-research-trust-an-/V0-001-007011234-3| title=Puerto Rico Science, Technology & Research Trust (Antigua Penitenciaria Estatal Oso Blanco) San Juan | website=eventful.com | publisher=Eventful | accessdate=5 December 2016 }}</ref>

The Trust is responsible for Puerto Rico’s public policy for [[science]], [[technology]], [[research and development]].{{fact|date=December 2016}} 

